<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Educational Content</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/education.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Financial Education Hub</h1>
            <p>Learn the basics of investing and financial planning</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    

    <main>
        <section id="overview">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Investing 101</h2>
                <p>Welcome to our beginner's guide to investing. Below are some key concepts to get you started:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>What is investing?</li>
                    <li>Why should you invest?</li>
                    <li>Types of investments</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="content">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Understanding ETFs</h2>
                <p>An ETF (Exchange-Traded Fund) is a type of investment fund that holds assets such as stocks, commodities, or bonds.</p>
                <p>ETFs are traded on stock exchanges similar to individual stocks, making them accessible to individual investors.</p>
                <button id="learnMoreBtn">Learn More</button>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="quiz">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Test Your Knowledge</h2>
                <p>Take our quiz to see how much you've learned about investing and ETFs!</p>
                <button id="startQuizBtn">Start Quiz</button>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2024 Financial Education Hub. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>

    <script>
        // Interactive functionalities (example)

        // Quiz button functionality
        document.getElementById('startQuizBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
            alert('Quiz starting soon!');
        });

        // Learn More button functionality
        document.getElementById('learnMoreBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
            alert('Learn more about ETFs!');
        });

    </script>
</body>
</html>
